{"id":14881057,"mediaExerciseId":"fa5b21dc-f94d-4ae8-9644-143e78afefa7","exerciseName":"8","chapterName":"7","chapterTitle":"Interest Rates and Bond Valuation","groupId":612313,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":233,"solutions":[{"id":6002978,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this task, **we should find the coupon rate of McConnell Corporation bonds.**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Coupon rates are determined by the entity that issues a bond. The coupon value will be the same for every future payment. So it is a fixed amount.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"We can use the formula for the price of the bonds, but we have to adjust it because the payments are semiannual.\n\n$$\\text{Price}=\\text{C}\\times\\dfrac{1-\\left(1+\\text{YTM}\\right)^\\text{-n}}{\\text{YTM}}+\\dfrac{\\text{P}}{\\left(1+\\text{YTM}\\right)^\\text{n}}$$\n\n$C$ - coupon of the bond \n\n$YTM$ - yield to maturity\n\n$P$ - par value\n\n$n$ - time","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"The payments are semiannual. We just need to divide the coupon rate by two because we will get paid twice per year. Also, YTM should be adjusted in the same way. But the period we should multiply by 2. In total, we will get paid not 14.5 times but 29 because of the semiannual payment.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":62,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/98198530fc22173d2f7a1a952342e202/09b143cafba242f40cacc37c742ee3b3/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":31,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/98198530fc22173d2f7a1a952342e202/09b143cafba242f40cacc37c742ee3b3/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's adjust the periods.\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{semiannual periods}&=\\text{annual periods}\\times2\\\\[15pt]\n&=14.5\\times2\\\\[15pt]\n&=29\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\n**We should insert in the formula 29 periods.**\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/98198530fc22173d2f7a1a952342e202/ddcf069c684900a3fc7c0dcb74b40e03/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/98198530fc22173d2f7a1a952342e202/ddcf069c684900a3fc7c0dcb74b40e03/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's adjust YTM.\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{semiannual YTM}&=\\dfrac{\\text{annual YTM}}{2}\\\\[15pt]\n&=\\dfrac{5.3\\%}{2}\\\\[15pt]\n&=\\boxed{2.65\\%}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\n**The semiannual YTM is 2.65\\%.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":327,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/98198530fc22173d2f7a1a952342e202/85c8f18a203b0bdf239624fe2c71e33e/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":165,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/98198530fc22173d2f7a1a952342e202/85c8f18a203b0bdf239624fe2c71e33e/lateximg.png","width":497}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's insert all the adjusted data in the formula for the bond price.\n\n\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n\\$1,045& =\\text{C}\\times\\dfrac{1-\\left(1+2.65\\%\\right)^\\text{-29}}{2.65\\%}+\\dfrac{\\$1,000}{\\left(1+2.65\\%\\right)^{29}}\\\\\n\\\\\n\\$1,045& =(\\text{C}\\times20.0614)+\\$468,374\\\\\n\\\\\n\\$1,045-\\$468,374&=\\text{C}\\times20.0614\\\\\n\\\\\n\\text{C}&=\\dfrac{\\$576.62}{20.0614}\\\\\n\\\\\n\\text{C}&=\\$28.74\\\\\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\n\nThe **annual** coupon value is \\$28.74.\n\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":141,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/98198530fc22173d2f7a1a952342e202/8d5c8298cf8fab5a0252af9b171a1f4b/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/98198530fc22173d2f7a1a952342e202/8d5c8298cf8fab5a0252af9b171a1f4b/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":7},{"columns":[{"text":"To get the semiannual coupon rate, we have to multiply by two the annual coupon rate and divide by face value.\n\n\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{semiannual coupon value}&=\\text{annual coupon value}\\times2\\\\[15pt]\n&=\\$28.74\\times2\\\\[15pt]\n&=\\$57.48\\\\[15pt]\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\n\n**The semiannual coupon value is $57.48.**\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":324,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/98198530fc22173d2f7a1a952342e202/da9888186c026557df63c449710f71db/lateximg_large.png","width":767},"regular":{"height":164,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/98198530fc22173d2f7a1a952342e202/da9888186c026557df63c449710f71db/lateximg.png","width":383}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":8},{"columns":[{"text":"Then, let us solve for the semiannual coupon rate. \n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{coupon rate}&=\\dfrac{\\$57.48}{\\$1,000}\\\\[15pt]\n&=0.05748\\times100\\\\[15pt]\n&=\\boxed{5.74\\%}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\n**The semiannual coupon rate is 5.74\\%.**\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":383,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/98198530fc22173d2f7a1a952342e202/70007bd7ea91c87730c4803022ee2645/lateximg_large.png","width":718},"regular":{"height":193,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/10/98198530fc22173d2f7a1a952342e202/70007bd7ea91c87730c4803022ee2645/lateximg.png","width":360}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":9}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"731afc96-1f4c-43bf-b082-d4d89227773b","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":9}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881058,"exerciseName":"9","page":233,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"b2b53620-aa5d-45d2-85a5-1c3635d64065","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-questions-and-problems-9-b2b53620-aa5d-45d2-85a5-1c3635d64065"},{"id":14881059,"exerciseName":"10","page":233,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"77206062-9a79-45d8-ba0a-c7ee62255096","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-questions-and-problems-10-77206062-9a79-45d8-ba0a-c7ee62255096"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881056,"exerciseName":"7","page":233,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"2e053a52-210d-4a10-8229-2a699d541d43","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-7-questions-and-problems-7-2e053a52-210d-4a10-8229-2a699d541d43"},{"id":14881055,"exerciseName":"6","page":233,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExe